  m_Name: Extensor_carpi_radialis_muscle.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Extensor_carpi_radialis_muscle.L
  partName: Extensor carpi radialis muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left extensor carpi radialis muscle is located along the cranial portion
    of the canine forearm and functions primarily to extend the carpal joint. Originating
    from the lateral humerus and inserting onto the metacarpal bones, this muscle
    plays a critical role in stabilizing the wrist during weight-bearing and locomotion.
  - It contributes to smooth forward limb movement by maintaining proper paw positioning
    during the stance phase of gait. The extensor carpi radialis also assists with
    shock absorption and coordinated forelimb mechanics during running and jumping
    activities.
